emotes.msg: awarding 1000 xp via the AwardXp emote!
you deserve mace experience! Have 1000 points of it! (If you don't have mace trained, it will be wasted.)
now, to test some more, give me a WaspWingGreen.
you deserve a point of missile defense! Hope you have it trained, or it will be wasted.
Have you completed the EmoteTestDrudgeKillerQuest twice?
Now I will see if you have done the EmoteTestSwordQuest three times!
I am removing the EmoteTestDrudgeKillerQuest from your quest table!
type @quests to make sure it is gone!
Give me a WaspWingMire to continue testing.
I am incrementing your EmoteTestDrudgeKillerQuest by 1.
type @quests to verify that this has been done one time.
Give me a WaspWingJungle to continue testing.
I am decrementing your EmoteTestDrudgeKillerQuest by 1.
type @quests to verify that this has now been done zero times.
Give me a Heaume to continue testing.
Here is a training credit! Wow!
Give me a Helmet to continue testing.
Thanks! Let me see if you are over level 20.
Give me a drudge charm and maybe I'll forgive you.
Now give me a male tusker token (TokenTuskerMale). But look at your deaths (on the burden panel) first.
I'm going to make you die 100 deaths.
You have died 100 times more! Ahahahah! (Check your burden panel to see how many times you have died.)
Now give me a female tusker token (TokenTuskerFemale).
Didn't like that, huh? Okay, okay, you didn't die 100 more times. (Check your deaths again.)
Now give me a tusker slave token (TokenTuskerSlave).
Instead of adding to your deaths, I can just set them. Here, you have died exactly 3 times.
Now give me a tusker guard token (TokenTuskerGuard).
Oooh, pretty! I'll give you something for that!
There you go! Enjoy your incomparable jewelry.
Let me see if you are attackable or don't have that quality
I will give you one of 4 somethings.
Starting all TEST events, then wait 1 minute for WEventController, please be patient
Starting Event tests, these tests are valid through January 1 2010
Give me a parchment to test some more!
(Alternatively, you can jump to the middle of testing by just giving me a WaspWingRed, or jump to the last phase by giving me a Helmet.)
This is %n's WorldBroadcast, announcing the UpdateQuestEmote successfully returned!
Give me another parchment within... oh... one minute (??), and I should say something different soon!
And while we're at it, lets check if you've completed the EmoteTestSwordQuest...
I see you've completed the EmoteTestSwordQuest!
Give me a WaspWingRed to get some mace experience! (And continue the tests.)
Yes, you have! You have completed the emote-test drudge quest twice!
to test more, give me a WaspWingBlue.
Yes, you have! You have completed the EmoteTestSwordQuest three times!
to test more, give me a WaspWingGold.
(I see you've done it two times. But two is not three.)
(I see you've done it one time. But one is not three.)
This is %n's LocalBroadcast. This is what happens when UpdateQuest successfully returns a QuestFailure!!
And while we're at it, lets check if you've completed the EmoteTestSwordQuest...
I see you have not completed the EmoteTestSwordQuest!
No, you haven't killed the emote-test drudge enough. You lamer!
Type "@Create EmoteTestDrudge". Kill the drudge. Do this again. Then come back and give me another green wing.
No, you haven't completed the EmoteTestSwordQuest THREE times... You lamer!
Pick up EmoteTestSword's until you have three of them. Give me a blue wasp wing after you pick each one up, and I'll comment differently depending on how many times you've completed the quest.
(You've never done it before at all. Zero is not three.)
20 or over! Now let me see if you are attackable.
You are attackable! Is your name Eric?
You are attackable! Is your name Eric?
Have you screwed with your acid resistance?
Looks like your RESIST_ACID float is about normal.
Now what about your max mana? Have you explicitly bought 50 points of mana? This won't count the mana gained from Self.
You have purchased 50 or more points of mana! Very nice!
But is your sword skill is over 100?
your sword skill is decent! Good!
More importantly, do you have mace trained?
Trained, it is! But to be a true warrior you need missile defense specialized.
Yes, well, that's something. Missile defense is specialized.
Now, let's see if your unbuffed Coordination is over 100.
How about your raw health, disregarding health gained from endurance?
raw max health is low -- less than 80.
Good thing you didn't give me any apples, I hate those.
Under 20! Now let me see if you are a attackable.
You are not attackable! Is your name Eric?
You are not attackable! Is your name Eric?
You are not named Eric! (You can change your name in the admin UI for testing purposes.)
Have you screwed with your acid resistance?
Hmm, you are a cheater! Your RESIST_ACID is abnormal!
Your strength is pitifully low. Less than 100!
Now what about your max mana? Have you explicitly bought 50 points of mana? This won't count the mana gained from Self.
I see you suck as a mage. You've bought less than 50 mana!
But is your sword skill is over 100?
Your sword skill is less than 100.
More importantly, do you have mace trained?
You don't have maced trained! You suck! Do you have missile defense specialized?
No, you don't have missile defense specialized. What a loser!
Now, let's see if your unbuffed Coordination is over 100.
How about your raw health, disregarding health gained from endurance?
raw max health is high -- 80 or more! Very impressive.
Good thing you didn't give me any apples, I hate those.
You must not have any experience to start this test, please create a new character.
The cow test is running! The cow test is running! Now I will test again.
The cow test is *still* running! Of course.
I think I'll just wander off a bit ...
The cow test is not running. How sad.
The cow test is not running. Damnit! I'm leaving!
you don't have the attackable boolean set! (This is correct)
Have a Merciless Monouga Idol (Danger, returning to NPC will produce infinite loop)
